mation is used in conjunction with numerical values of the first few moments.

Small-x problem and the Regge limit 2.6

(See e.g. the review [109].) One considers structure functions of deeply inelastic scattering at small x
where the amplitude is expected to be most sensitive to self-interaction of gluons:

F(x,Q2 ) for x with Q2
