X .






Note that the "small" parameter need not be nu merically small; it is only important that one performs an
expansion with respect to such a parameter, and that the expansion works within desired accuracy for
the values of interest.
There is no general theory of the quasi-elastic regime; only some leading-logarithm results are avail-
able (see e.g. [95]). Note that in the small-x region the parton model is not expected to work anyway.
On the other hand, the quasi-elastic regime is, in principle, no worse than the standard parton-model re-
gime.

