QCD jets 2.17

The concept of jets in the processes at high energies is the key element of the important paradigm in
the physics of elementary particles that has given rise to many interesting problems (see e.g. the review
[116]). In practice, one deals here with cross sections of parton type with many soft and collinear sin-
gularities.
Below an example of asymptotic expansion problem is given, which is rather different from those al-
ready considered.

The double-box problemi 2.18

